the d-pawn brings a pawn away from the center but black can develop his bishop 
with less limitations} bxc6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Re1 d6 {to try and activate the light 
squared bishop.} 7. e5 {Charges forward.} d5 8. h3 {Removes Bg4 as a 
possibility.} Bf5 9. d3 {The bishop is completely controlled. As long as white 
tries to limit black's dark squared bishop, then he should be fine in this 
position.} *

