the d-pawn brings a pawn away from the center but black can develop his bishop 
with less limitations} bxc6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Re1 e5 {Trying to prevent e5. This 
does however limit the dark squared bishop.} 7. c3 {Prepares d4.} Ne7 8. d4 cxd4 
9. cxd4 exd4 10. Nxd4 O-O {Entering a position where white's pawn structure is 
secure and much better.} 11. Nc3 $14 {White is slightly better here. His knights 
are out and his dark squared bishop has free development.} *

