the dark squares in white's position. Black has no way to exploit this. And the 
bishop on c1 is flexible. Remember: This is appropriate in THIS position, does 
not mean you should weaken your dark squares in random positions like this.This 
move has a purpose to play c4!} Ng6 8. O-O Be7 9. c4 O-O 10. Bb2 *

