1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 {This has the idea of bringing the knight into e7 
to support the knight on c6. This is too slow however, and white can take the 
bishop immediately.} 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. b3 $5 {An interesting idea that was played 
by many players before such as Carlsen and Caruana. The idea is to Fianchetto 
the bishop on b2 and extert pressure down the center that way. This may come as 
a surprise to players who only study main line theory.} Ne7 {Bringing the knight 
