12. Kd1 Qxa1 13. Qxc8 Qxb1 14. Qd7+ Ne7 {Only worsens his position. Although 
black is up a piece, white is going to try to checkmate black. The queen on b1 
is completely offside.} 15. Re1 Qxa2 16. Qxe6+ Ke8 17. d4 cxd4 18. Re5 {With the 
beautiful idea of Rb5 to threaten mate.} d3 19. Rc5 Kd8 20. Bg5 {Black will have 
to surrender his queen to survive.} *

