12. Kd1 Qxa1 13. Qxc8 Qxb1 14. Qd7+ Be7 15. Re1 {Black is a piece up, but white 
has completely paralyzed the kingside. Black cannot even develop properly 
because of the threats on e6.} Qa1 {Black has to get his queen back into the 
game.} 16. Qxe6+ Kf8 17. Qc8+ Kf7 18. Qxg4 Qf6 19. Re3 Qd6 20. Qc8 $16 {White is 
close to winning, he just needs to keep black's kingside paralyzed. His rook and 
queen are active, his bishop on c1 can develop to b2 and become a monster.} *

