e5. As well as weakening d6.} Be7 9. Nc3 c4 {Once again this sacrifice is 
interesting, but offers black very little.} 10. Ne4 {Rather than taking and 
damaging our own structure, we can play Ne4 to control the dark squares.} c5 11. 
Nfg5 Qc7 {Grafl-Kalinitschew 2005. Grafl played the dubious move Nd6+? which 
black simply exchanged off. Black was fine there. But he couldve continued the 
attack with Qf3!} 12. Qf3 Rf8 13. Nd6+ Bxd6 14. exd6 {Now because the queen is 
on f3, the rook on a8 is hanging.} Qb7 15. Bxg7 Qxf3 16. gxf3 Rg8 17. Bf6 Bb7 *

