6. c3 {preparing d4 at some stage.} Nf6 {Black in this position is always 
looking to play d5 at some point to fix his structure and repair the weaknesses 
he has with his pawn structure.} 7. Re1 Bg4 8. h3 Bh5 {Preserving the bishop.} 
9. d4 $1 {breaking in the center. White needs to get this move in as soon as 
possible to contest the center.} cxd4 10. cxd4 {The threat is now to play dxe5 
followed by g4 and Nxe5 winning a pawn.} Nd7 {defending the e-pawn.} 11. Nbd2 
{With the idea of playing Nc4 and pressuring e5. As well as playing e3.} exd4 {A 
dubious move.} 12. Qa4 $1 {Attacks both pawns.} c5 13. e5 $1 {dxe5 runs into 
Nxe5 with a discovered attack incoming.} d5 14. e6 $1 fxe6 15. Rxe6+ Be7 16. Ne5 
