{White is NOT losing material here. I will discuss this trap.} 8. Bb2 Qxb2 {It 
looks like white is losing a piece. Or even another piece. But actually this is 
completely fine for white.} 9. Nc3 Qa3 {Trying to escape with the queen.} 10. 
Qf3 {This attacks c6 and f7 at the same time. Black has to concede something.} 
Ne7 11. Qxf7+ Kd8 {There is no immediate move. Simple castling should be enough 
to kill off black.} 12. O-O Qa6 13. Qh5 {Threatening a fork. As long as each 
move that white makes is a threat, white should be winning.} g6 14. Nf7+ Ke8 15. 
Nd6+ Kd7 16. Qe5 {Attacking the rook.} Rg8 17. Nce4 {Threatening Nxc5.} Bg7 18. 
Nxc5+ Kd8 19. Ndb7+ $1 {This threatens Qd6 check and Nxa6.} Qxb7 20. Nxb7+ Bxb7 
21. Qd6+ Ke8 22. Rae1 $18 *

