[White "Qb6 rare line Kan"]
[Black "type sacrifice"]
[Result "*"]
[SourceTitle "06 Rare lines"]
[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "sicilian-rossolimo-for-white/course/5314, variation/208031"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Qb6 4. Nc3 e6 {This move e6 transposes into a Kan 
variation where white is simply a tempo up. And that gives white a good edge.} 
5. Bxc6 Qxc6 6. d4 $1 cxd4 7. Nxd4 {This was the point of Nc3. To defend e4. Now 
the black queen has to move back.} Qc7 8. O-O a6 9. Re1 {In this Kan variation 
white is a tempo up. Black still has to castle and develop. The only piece 
developed for black is his queen, and his light squared bishop is suffering on 
c8.} d6 10. Bf4 $1 {This is a very nice move to give white a good edge in the 
position.} e5 $6 {It seems like white is losing a piece, but in fact, he is 
completely fine here.} 11. Nd5 $1 {Hitting the queen} Qb8 12. Bg3 {Stepping away 
from the pawn.} exd4 $2 13. e5 $1 {With the threat of exd6.} Be6 14. exd6 Bxd6 
15. Qg4 $1 {Attacking g7.} Bxg3 16. Rxe6+ fxe6 17. Qxe6+ Kf8 18. fxg3 {To open 
up the f-file for the rook.} Qe8 19. Qd6+ Kf7 20. Rf1+ Nf6 21. Rxf6+ gxf6 22. 
Qxf6+ Kg8 23. Ne7+ Qxe7 24. Qxe7 $18 *

